[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Purging flax</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an annual
European plant of the genus <gen>Linum</gen> (<spn>Linum
catharticum</spn>); dwarf wild flax; -- so called from its use as a
cathartic medicine.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purging</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Purging
<hw>Pur"ging</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The act of
cleansing; excessive evacuations; especially, diarrhea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

